Author: MissNietzsche
Text: Don't brush your teeth straight after, wait at least 30 mins  Rinse with water and baking soda right after though  Take like 2 Tums and drink lots of water right after  Buy children's mouthwash because they have more fluoride than the adult versions  Try not to throw up pure stomach acid for the sake of making sure you got every bit of food up  Make sure to take really good care of your teeth when you're not b/p'ing by brushing and flossing regularly  If you get acid reflux, and it becomes an ongoing issue, make sure it gets addressed by a doctor
